com.pump.geom.area

Class AreaXBody

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.geom.area.AreaXBody

  • public class AreaXBody
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a list of CurveX segments that makes up the shape of an AreaX.

    This is based on the Vector named "curves" in the original java.awt.geom.Area class. However this class has a few key modifications:

    • The bounds are internally updated constantly.
    • The methods to add curves are protected. So while this list can be iterated over via public methods, it is immutable to classes outside this package. This is a deliberate choice to facilitate the AreaXRules model.
    • This object adds the concept of validation (more on this below).
    • This object is not synchronized. The AreaX class is, but this class is not. This is for internal behind-the-scenes work: it is the caller's responsibility to synchronize method calls safely.

    Validation

    This concept is new to the AreaX package, but the code is not new. The original Area class automatically validated everything all the time. Here I separated this process because -- as we start dealing with complex AreaXRules -- we can get some performance improvements if we don't validate all shapes.

    A "valid" body is one that has been primed for geometric operations. An "invalid" body is one that has not yet been primed -- it is a raw dump of another shape.

    In the end: all shapes that are involved in computing an add, xor, intersect or subtract are validated. But we don't have to perform an expensive validation in order to see whether Shape A contains Shape B.

    • Field Detail

      • elementData

        protected CurveX[] elementData
        The array buffer into which the components of the list are stored. The capacity of the list is the length of this array buffer, and is at least large enough to contain all the list elements.

        This array must be of type type.

        Any array elements following the last element in the list are null.

      • elementCount

        protected int elementCount
        The number of valid components in this list. Components elementData[0] through elementData[elementCount-1] are the actual items.

      • isValidated

        public boolean isValidated()
        Returns whether this body is validated or not.

        Validation is an expensive process of restructuring a primitive AreaXBody so it is primed for geometric operations.

      • validate

        public AreaXBody validate()
        This returns a validated copy of this object. If this body is already validated, then this object is returned.

        If this object is invalid but this method has already been performed, then the previously created object is returned.

        Otherwise: this body is validated. This is expensive but required for other operations.

      • ensureCapacity

        protected void ensureCapacity(int minCapacity)
        Increases the capacity of this list, if necessary, to ensure that it can hold at least the number of components specified by the minimum capacity argument.

        If the current capacity of this list is less than minCapacity, then its capacity is increased by replacing its internal data array, kept in the field elementData, with a larger one. The size of the new data array will be the old size plus capacityIncrement, unless the value of capacityIncrement is less than or equal to zero, in which case the new capacity will be twice the old capacity; but if this new size is still smaller than minCapacity, then the new capacity will be minCapacity.

        Parameters:
        minCapacity - the desired minimum capacity.
